result.execSummary:
The defendant Jase M. Brawner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).
  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Fines are to be paid as follows:  $500 due on or before May 15, 2015 and then $100 due by the 1st of each month beginning June 1, 2015 and then on the 1st of each month thereafter until paid in full.  Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.

Must submit a DNA sample and pay the surcharge.  Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.  This has been added to the payment plan.

records.addlTxt: DNA Proof of Submission form signed by JASO Official

Defendant appeared with counsel Robert Osborne.  ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Joint recommendation for resolution.  Count 1 - 3 of 14CF168 to be amended by removing the domestic abuse enhancer and defendant will plead no contest to those counts; Count 4 of 14CF168 to be dismissed and read-in.  Case 14CF201 to be dismissed and read-in.  Court reviews amended charges/penalties with defendant.  Court reviews elements/plea questionnaire/waiver of rights.  Court accepts waiver of rights and finds the pleas were entered freely, voluntarily, and intelligently.  Finding of guilty on 14CF168 counts 1-3 as amended; count 4 dismissed and read-in; 14CF201 also dismissed and read-in.  Defendant speaks.  Judge explaine there is still an injuction in effect until November 2016 so no contact until expiration.  Joint recommendation of $250 fine + court costs on each count with a $200 DNA surcharge assessed on Count 1.  Defendant is to pay $500 by May 15, 2015 and then to pay $100 per month commencing June 1st and each month thereafter by the 1st of each month until paid in full.  Failure to pay in full by the due date will result in serving 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.
